[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Morrill defeated the Democratic candidate William P.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] One-term Unionist Anthony Kennedy was elected in 1856 or 1857.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The Maryland General Assembly met on March 5, 1862, to hold an election for the next term.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Voting proceeded separately in the Senate and the House of Delegates, after which the tellers withdrew and to count the ballots in the Senate chamber.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The Union candidate Reverdy Johnson was elected on the first ballot.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Two-term Republican Charles Sumner was re-elected in 1857.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The Republican state convention met at Worcester, Massachusetts, on September 9, 1862.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Sumner had earned the disapproval of Conservative Republicans when he opposed Lincoln's plan for gradual emancipation in March 1862, calling instead for Congress to use its authority under the War Powers Clause to abolish slavery immediately.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Seeking to preempt a movement to replace Sumner at the next senatorial election, Sumner's allies took the unusual step of having the state convention endorse his bid for re-election.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] A resolution endorsing Sumner and approving his record in the Senate passed over the protests of Conservative delegates, in effect making Sumner's re-election the central issue of the fall campaign.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Conservative opponents of Sumner held a convention at Boston on October 7, 1862.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Many of the organizers of the convention were former Whigs who had supported the Constitutional Union Party in 1860.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] In a nod to antipartisan wartime rhetoric, the movement called itself the People's Party; its express purpose was to defeat Sumner's bid for reelection.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The convention adopted a pro-war, anti-abolitionist platform and selected candidates for the upcoming state elections; Charles F.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Adams was nominated for U.S. senator, but declined.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Following these events, most Conservative Republicans returned to the fold, and the Republican ticket was elected by a large majority.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The Senate and the House of Representatives met separately on January 15, 1863, to hold an election for the next term.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Sumner defeated the People's candidate Josiah G.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] There were two elections in Michigan, due to the death of Kinsley S.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Bingham died on October 5, 1861, causing a special election.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] The Republican members of the legislature held a caucus on January 3, 1862.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Wells, and Henry Waldron were the leading candidates.
[src:1863-west-virginia-gubernatorial-election/1862-63-united-states-senate-elections] Howard was nominated on the sixth ballot.
